tory of science, he was also an astonishingly wide-ranging political and cultural figure. From his attack on Spiritualism to his failed voyage to the Arctic and his near-mythical hot-air balloon trip, this is the story of an extraordinary maverick. The ideals that shaped his work outside science also led Mendeleev to order the elements and, eventually, to engineer one of the most fascinating scientific developments of the nineteenth century. A Well-Ordered Thing is a classic work that tells the story of one of the world’s most important minds.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aChemistszRussia (Federation)vBiography. 0aPeriodic law. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Science & Technology.2bisacsh  aAcademy of Sciences.  aDmitrii Mendeleev.  aEuropean science.  aGreat Reforms.  aImperial Academy of Sciences.  aImperial Petersburg.  aImperial Russia.  aImperial systems.  aMediumistic Phenomena.  aRussia.  aRussian Chemical Society.  aRussian Physical Society.  aRussian Spiritualism.  aRussian chauvinism.  aRussian culture.  aRussian education.  aRussian stability.  aSpiritualism.  aSt. Petersburg University.  aSt. Petersburg.  aautocracy.  abureaucracy.  achemistry.  aclassification.  acultural conflict.  aeducational reform.  agas laws.  ageneral examinations.  ahistory of science.  aindividual innovation.  aliberalism.  amaverick.  aperiodic law.  aperiodic system.  aperiodic table.  aphysics.  areligion.  arule of law.  ascientific societies.  aseances.  astudent rebellion.  asuperstition.  ateaching.  atechnology.  atsarist regime.  auniversality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z978311